<TITLE> Trust Bank cuts lending rate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)Trust Bank has cut down lending rate for its business loan schemes, according to a statement by the bank on Wednesday. From now, export financing will be available at 7 percent, women entrepreneur loan at 9 percent, agriculture credit and SME loan at 10 percent, corporate credit between 11.5 and 13 percent, home mortgage loan at 13 percent and Trade Financing from 12 to13 percent. The move is part of the bank's decision to take the lead in supporting the business community and potential business clients in the wake of the global economic slowdown, the statement quoted managing director Iqbal U Ahmed. The interest rate cut came in line with the bank's mission to reach and support all businesses in the country, reads the release. The statement further said the bank prioritises diversifying credit portfolio across the borrowers and sectors to add economic value of its business activities. The bank management has attached immense importance for small and medium enterprises that have a huge growth potentialityif their credit is ensured under soft terms and conditions, says the release.
